<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Questionable status. In the Mediterranean, only reported from Greece (
<bibRefCitation author="Kisseleva, MI" journalOrPublisher="Studies of Sevastopol Biological Station" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="135 - 146" title="Qualitative and quantitative distribution of the benthos in the area surrounding Dardanelles, Aegean Sea" volume="14" year="1961">Kisseleva 1961</bibRefCitation>
). Record doubted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Arvanitidis, Christos" journalOrPublisher="PhD thesis. Aristotle University of Thessaloniki, Thessaloniki" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Συστηματική και βιονομική μελέτη των μακροβενθικών πολυxαίτων (AnnelidaPolychaeta) του Βορείου Αιγαίου" year="1994">Arvanitidis (1994)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Cinar, Melih Ertan" journalOrPublisher="Turkish Journal of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="1 - 31" title="Check-List of Annelida from the Coasts of Turkey" volume="38" year="2014">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Çınar">Cinar</normalizedToken>
et al. (2014)
</bibRefCitation>
based on the species' ecology: 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Alkmaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Alkmaria romijni" order="Terebellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="romijni">Alkmaria romijni</taxonomicName>
is typically a brackish water species but has been reported from a depth of 65-100 m in the open waters of the Aegean Sea.
</paragraph>
